2020-02-04 network-manager 1.2.2-24

  [ Alfonso Sanchez-Beato <alfonso.sanchez-beato@canonical.com> ]
  * Stage only copyright of staged packages
    Some copyright files were not needed as they come from packages from
    which we do not take any file.
    
    Do not stage libsqlite3
    libsqlite3 is already included in the core snap.
    
    Add unstage.txt file
    This file contains a list of debian package that we are not actually
    staging, although snapcraft adds them to manifest.yaml. CI now
    recognizes this file, and manually removes the listed packages from the
    manifest when releasing a snap to the store.
    Merge-Proposal: https://code.launchpad.net/~alfonsosanchezbeato/snappy-hwe-snaps/+git/network-manager/+merge/377873
  * NOTICE: CVE-2018-15688 was fixed in 1.2.2-20
    CVE-2018-15688 / USN-3807-1 was fixed in 1.2.2-20, although
    the Changelog for that version did not reflect the fact.
    - CVE-2018-15688
    Merge-Proposal: https://code.launchpad.net/~alfonsosanchezbeato/snappy-hwe-snaps/+git/network-manager/+merge/378035

  [ Changes in staged packages ]
  
  libdbus-1-3: not staged anymore
  
  libglib2.0-0: not staged anymore
  
  libnss3-nssdb: not staged anymore
  
  libffi6: not staged anymore
  
2020-01-17 network-manager 1.2.2-23

  [ Alfonso Sanchez-Beato <alfonso.sanchez-beato@canonical.com> ]
  * Strip binaries for a smaller snap
    Merge-Proposal: https://code.launchpad.net/~alfonsosanchezbeato/snappy-hwe-snaps/+git/network-manager/+merge/354491
  * snap: copy changelog to the package
    Merge-Proposal: https://code.launchpad.net/~alfonsosanchezbeato/snappy-hwe-snaps/+git/network-manager/+merge/372525
  * Do not stage libraries that are part already of the core snap and that
    in fact we were not even including in the snap. This will remove some
    dependencies from the manifest so we will not get CVEs for these libs
    that do not actually affect us.
    
    Use documented way of specifying slots and hooks
    
    Remove calls to set log level in wrapper:
    The calls were actually failing as NM was not started yet. Furthermore,
    the log level is set via a call option in NM. Also remove nmcli-internal
    as after this it is not used anymore and probably there will be no need
    for it in the future (we restart always NM when the settings change
    instead of dynamically changing it).
    
    test: debug-config-option: robustify and fix:
    '!' does not have the expected effect with 'set -e'. Also, wait a bit
    when NM is re-starting. Ideally we should wait for it to appear on DBus
    though.
    Merge-Proposal: https://code.launchpad.net/~alfonsosanchezbeato/snappy-hwe-snaps/+git/network-manager/+merge/377715

