  [ Roberto Mier Escandón  <roberto.escandon@canonical.com> ]
  * Debug enable/disable config option.
    
    You can restart network-manager service in debug mode by:
      snap set network-manager debug.enable=true
    
    and disable debug mode:
      snap set network-manager debug.enable=false
    
    Default value is false.
    
    When set to true, service is started with these flags:
      --debug --log-level=DEBUG
    
    NOTE: Additionally, there are some spread tests changes to make them more stable
    Merge-Proposal: https://code.launchpad.net/~rmescandon/snappy-hwe-snaps/+git/network-manager/+merge/327096
  * debug config option back to debug.enable
    spread tests operations being repeated use now a common helper function
    Merge-Proposal: https://code.launchpad.net/~rmescandon/snappy-hwe-snaps/+git/network-manager/+merge/327866

